#. type: Table
#: _generated-doc/main/config/quarkus-aesh-ssh.adoc
msgid ""
"[[quarkus-aesh-ssh_quarkus-aesh-ssh-password]] [.property-path]##link:#quarkus-aesh-ssh_quarkus-aesh-ssh-password[`+++quarkus.aesh.ssh.password+++`]##\n"
"config_property_copy_button:+++quarkus.aesh.ssh.password+++[]\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"[.description]\n"
"--\n"
"Password for SSH authentication. If not set, any password is accepted (suitable for development only).\n"
"\n"
"For production, use public key authentication via `authorized-keys-file` instead. If password authentication is needed, avoid storing the password in plaintext in `application.properties`. Instead, reference an environment variable:\n"
"\n"
"```\n"
"quarkus.aesh.ssh.password=${SSH_PASSWORD}\n"
"```\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"Environment variable: env_var_with_copy_button:+++QUARKUS_AESH_SSH_PASSWORD+++[]\n"
"--"
msgstr ""

#. type: Table
#: _generated-doc/main/config/quarkus-aesh-ssh.adoc
msgid ""
"[[quarkus-aesh-ssh_quarkus-aesh-ssh-authorized-keys-file]] [.property-path]##link:#quarkus-aesh-ssh_quarkus-aesh-ssh-authorized-keys-file[`+++quarkus.aesh.ssh.authorized-keys-file+++`]##\n"
"config_property_copy_button:+++quarkus.aesh.ssh.authorized-keys-file+++[]\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"[.description]\n"
"--\n"
"Path to an OpenSSH-format authorized_keys file for public key authentication. This is the recommended authentication method for production environments. When set, clients can authenticate with a private key whose public key is listed in this file. Can be used alongside password authentication.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"Environment variable: env_var_with_copy_button:+++QUARKUS_AESH_SSH_AUTHORIZED_KEYS_FILE+++[]\n"
"--"
msgstr ""

